     1	//! Generic row-kernel operator framework.
     2	//!
     3	//! Every nonlinear family decomposes its coefficient-space Hessian as
     4	//!
     5	//! ```text
     6	//! H_β = Σ_i  Jᵢᵀ Hᵢ Jᵢ
     7	//! ```
     8	//!
     9	//! where Hᵢ is a small (K×K) row Hessian in "primary space" and Jᵢ is the
    10	//! (sparse, linear) row Jacobian mapping coefficients → primary scalars.
    11	//!
    12	//! The [`RowKernel<K>`] trait captures the family-specific parts:
    13	//!   - the analytic kernel (NLL, gradient, Hessian per row)
    14	//!   - the Jacobian wiring (forward, adjoint, quadratic pullback, diagonal)
    15	//!   - higher-order contracted derivatives (3rd, 4th) for REML outer
    16	//!
    17	//! All assembly — gradient, matvec, diagonal, dense Hessian, directional
    18	//! derivatives — is then generic over any `RowKernel<K>`.
