  7569	    /// The Gaussian location-scale joint Hessian depends on β because the
  7570	    /// cross-block (μ,log σ) and (log σ,log σ) blocks contain the residual
  7571	    /// r = y − μ (via the row scalars m = r·w and n = r²·w), which changes
  7572	    /// when β_μ moves.  The (μ,μ) block weight w = 1/σ² also depends on
  7573	    /// β_{log σ}.  This override is essential for correct M_j[u] drift
  7574	    /// corrections when ψ hyperparameters move the design matrices.
