The basic survival likelihoods I’ve read so far are using the standard `log H` Royston-Parmar form: interval contribution `H_exit - H_entry`, event contribution `eta_exit + log eta_dot`. I haven’t found a definite sign/formula error there yet, so I’m moving into the transformation-normal and marginal-slope kernels where missing Jacobians or chain-rule terms are more likely.
