    80	// De-nested cubic transport kernel.
    81	//
    82	// This module implements the de-nested flexible-link/score-warp model
    83	//
    84	//   eta(z) = a + b*z + b*delta_h(z) + delta_w(a + b*z)
    85	//
    86	// where delta_h is the score warp and delta_w is the link deviation.
    87	// This is not the literal nested composition L(a + b*H(z)); it is an
    88	// additive-correction model around the affine core a + b*z.
    89	//
    90	// On each partition cell, both deviations are cubic polynomials, so eta is
    91	// at most sextic in z and q(z) = 0.5*(z^2 + eta^2) is at most degree 12.
    92	// The integral of exp(-q(z)) is evaluated by transporting from the affine
    93	// anchor (c2=c3=0, where q is Gaussian and the integral reduces to BVN)
    94	// to the target non-affine cell via the polynomial moment recurrence.
    95	//
    96	// The partition covers (-∞, +∞) with:
    97	//   • two semi-infinite affine TAIL cells (outside all deviation support),
    98	//   • finitely many interior cells (each a sextic microcell).
    99	// Because tail cells have constant deviations (c2=c3=0), their bounds
   100	// are parameter-independent, so no Leibniz boundary-motion corrections
   101	// appear in the derivatives.
   102	//
   103	// Shared by bernoulli_marginal_slope and survival_marginal_slope families.
   104	
   105	#[derive(Clone, Copy, Debug, PartialEq)]
