**FINDINGS**

1. [src/families/latent_survival.rs](/Users/user/gam/src/families/latent_survival.rs:2638)  
   Wrong expression: `neg_hess_scale: survival / event_prob,`  
   Correct expression: `neg_hess_scale: -survival / event_prob,` or reuse `grad_scale`.  
   Derivation: for event `1`, with `t = log S`, `ℓ(t)=log(1-exp(t))`, so `ℓ' = -S/(1-S)` and `ℓ'' = -S/(1-S)^2`. If `survival_jet.neg_hessian = -t''`, then `-∇²ℓ = ℓ'(-t'') - ℓ'' t't'`, so the coefficient on `survival_jet.neg_hessian` is `ℓ' = -S/(1-S)`, not `+S/(1-S)`. The wrong positive factor is consumed at [line 3570](/Users/user/gam/src/families/latent_survival.rs:3570), [line 3585](/Users/user/gam/src/families/latent_survival.rs:3585), and [line 3590](/Users/user/gam/src/families/latent_survival.rs:3590).  
   Severity: definitive.

2. [src/families/family_meta.rs](/Users/user/gam/src/families/family_meta.rs:37)  
   Wrong expression: `InverseLink::Standard(LinkFunction::Log) => LikelihoodFamily::PoissonLog,`  
   Correct expression: this binomial resolver must not return a Poisson family. The correct model is a binomial response with log inverse link, e.g. `LikelihoodSpec::new(ResponseFamily::Binomial, InverseLink::Standard(LinkFunction::Log))`, or an unsupported-link error if legacy `LikelihoodFamily` cannot represent it.  
   Derivation: Bernoulli/binomial log-link likelihood is `y log μ + (1-y) log(1-μ)` with `μ=exp(η)`. Poisson log-link likelihood is `yη - exp(η) - log(y!)`. These are not the same distribution or likelihood.  
   Severity: definitive.

3. [src/families/family_meta.rs](/Users/user/gam/src/families/family_meta.rs:22) and [src/families/family_meta.rs](/Users/user/gam/src/families/family_meta.rs:49)  
   Wrong expressions: `InverseLink::Standard(LinkFunction::Identity) => InverseLink::Standard(LinkFunction::Logit),` and `InverseLink::Standard(LinkFunction::Identity) => LikelihoodFamily::BinomialLogit,`  
   Correct expression: preserve the identity link as `InverseLink::Standard(LinkFunction::Identity)` if supported, or reject it. It must not be silently changed to logit.  
   Derivation: identity inverse link is `μ=η`; logit inverse link is `μ=1/(1+exp(-η))`. Substituting logit changes the likelihood surface, derivatives, fitted probabilities, and any downstream deviance/REML geometry.  
   Severity: definitive.
